text.section:
A specialized rescue squad may engage in a general rescue squad activity if:
That activity is specified in its mission statement;
The rescue squad has twelve (12) persons including a commanding officer from within the membership of the specialized rescue squad whose mission statement is to engage in the general rescue squad activity;
The persons assigned to the general rescue squad activity meet the training requirements specified by statute and administrative regulation;
The rescue squad has the equipment required by administrative regulation to engage in general rescue squad activity as listed in its mission statement; and
The rescue squad has a vehicle for transporting the required equipment to the scene.
